-- nested class
-- putting the speciality tool inside the toolbox.

3 types of nested class
-- Inner Class,
-- Static Nested Class
-- Anonymous Class


1.inner class
-- it can belongs to instance of outer class,
-- it can access the methods and variables of the outer class

2.static nested class
-- A static nested class is associated with the Outer Class itself
-- it can't access the non static variables of the outer class
because it doesn't have a this keyword to reference to an object

3.Anonymous Class
this is a class with no name.
-- it is for the one-time use
you declare and instantiate it at the same time.
